{
  "info": {
    "name": "Real-Time Vocabulary Quiz API",
    "_postman_id": "e1f2a3b4-c5d6-47e8-9a0b-1c2d3e4f5a6b",
    "description": "Contract-first API collection for the Real-Time Vocabulary Quiz server.\n\nEvery request maps to a testable scenario in `docs/02-test-cases.md`. The HTTP control/query surface makes all request/response cases assertable in Postman; the real-time push channel is documented in the **Realtime (WebSocket)** folder.\n\n## Auth\nUsers are pre-authenticated (mocked, per the challenge). Identity is supplied as `user_id` (WebSocket query param) or the `X-User-ID` header (HTTP). There is no token to send. Collection auth = No Auth.\n\n## Variables\n- `baseUrl` (default `http://localhost:8080`)\n- `wsUrl` (default `ws://localhost:8080`)\n- `quizId`, `userId`, `otherUserId` — auto-populated by the Create/Join requests' test scripts.\n\n## Error body shape\n```json\n{ \"code\": \"duplicate_answer\", \"message\": \"Answer already submitted for this question\" }\n```\n\n## Note\nThe HTTP/WebSocket layer is the next implementation increment; this collection is the contract it will satisfy (the domain/store/service core that backs it is already implemented and tested).",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
  "variable": [
    { "key": "baseUrl", "value": "http://localhost:8080" },
    { "key": "wsUrl", "value": "ws://localhost:8080" },
    { "key": "quizId", "value": "" },
    { "key": "userId", "value": "alice" },
    { "key": "otherUserId", "value": "bob" }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
